        "user": "Here is the canonical definition of \"prismatic affinity\": Prismatic affinity is the property of a perceived object whose apparent identity shifts coherently with the angle of attention given to it, such that two observers attending under different framings produce non-overlapping but internally consistent descriptions, distinguishing it from ambiguity (which is undecided meaning) and from perspective-dependence (which is observer position alone). Acknowledge that you have read it.",
